### Feature hasn't been suggested before.

- [x] I have verified this feature I'm about to request hasn't been suggested before.

### Describe the enhancement you want to request

## Problem

The VSCode extension's `KiloConnectionService` always spawns its own `kilo serve` child process via `ServerManager`, binding to `http://127.0.0.1:<random_port>`. There is no way to point the extension at a pre-existing `kilo serve` running on a remote host.

Specifically in `packages/kilo-vscode/src/services/cli-backend/`:

- `server-manager.ts:109` hardcodes `spawn(cliPath, ["serve", "--port", "0"])` with no override path
- `connection-service.ts:679` hardcodes `` baseUrl: `http://127.0.0.1:${server.port}` ``
- `doConnect()` unconditionally calls `this.serverManager.getServer()` — no branch to skip local spawn

## Use Case

Running `kilo serve` on a remote VPS as a systemd service, reachable over a private mesh VPN (e.g. Netbird/Tailscale), and connecting the local VSCodium extension panel to it directly over HTTP — without needing `open-remote-ssh` or any SSH tunnel.

This is a natural fit: `kilo serve` already exposes a complete HTTP+SSE API, and the browser UI can connect to it fine. The extension panel should be able to as well.

## Proposed Change

Add two VSCode settings:

```
kilo-code.new.serverUrl      (string, default: "")
kilo-code.new.serverPassword (string, default: "")
```

In `doConnect()`, check `serverUrl` before calling `serverManager.getServer()`:

```typescript
private async doConnect(workspaceDir: string): Promise<void> {
  this.resetConnection()

  const externalUrl = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration("kilo-code.new").get<string>("serverUrl", "").trim()
  const externalPassword = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration("kilo-code.new").get<string>("serverPassword", "").trim()

  let config: ServerConfig
  if (externalUrl) {
    config = { baseUrl: externalUrl, password: externalPassword }
    // skip ServerManager entirely — no child process spawned
  } else {
    const server = await this.serverManager.getServer()
    this.info = { port: server.port }
    config = { baseUrl: `http://127.0.0.1:${server.port}`, password: server.password }
  }
  // ... rest of doConnect unchanged
```

The health poll, SSE adapter, and SDK client all already work against any `baseUrl` — no changes needed there.

## Why It's Low-Risk

- Zero behavioural change when `serverUrl` is not set (default path unchanged)
- The HTTP+SSE protocol is already fully abstracted behind `KiloClient` / `SdkSSEAdapter`
- `handleServerExit` only fires from `ServerManager`'s `onExit` callback, which is never registered in the external path — clean separation

## Note on `ServerInstance.process`

The `ServerInstance` type currently requires a `ChildProcess`. If keeping `ServerManager` as the sole `ServerInstance` producer is preferred, an alternative is a new `ExternalServerInstance` type (or making `process` optional) — either works.

