### Description

Problem: Kilo queries http://localhost:<port>/v1/models (OpenAI-compatible) which returns only {id, object, owned_by} with no context info. It should use LM Studio's native endpoint http://localhost:<port>/api/v1/models which includes loaded instance configuration.

Impact: Kilo defaults to a large fallback (200K+) for context window size. Compaction doesn't trigger at the configured LM Studio value (115K). User sees tokens accumulating without compaction: 66.7K / 262.1K with no compaction activity.

Expected: Kilo should detect LM Studio by checking /api/v1/models and use loaded_instances[].config.context_length for the active model's context limit, falling back to max_context_length if not loaded.

Configured context length in LM Studio UI: 115,132 tokens
Kilo default fallback used instead: ~262,000+ tokens


Suggested Fixes
Add LM Studio provider detection that queries api/v1/models and parses loaded_instances[].config.context_length as the context window size
Consider adding a context_window override in kilo.json for providers that don't advertise it via /v1/models

### Plugins

_No response_

