# Local fix

# Fix: Premature Session Termination with Qwen3.5 27B

## Problem

When using `Qwen/Qwen3.5-27B` model via OpenAI-compatible API, the agent would prematurely terminate after tool call execution. Users were forced to type "continue" to resume work.

## Analysis

Logs revealed the following sequence:

```
finish-step: stop
loop check: { lastAssistantFinish: "stop", ... }
exiting loop: { finish: "stop", ... }
```

**Root Cause**: The Qwen3.5 27B model, after executing a tool call, was responding with an empty message containing `finish_reason="stop"` (without any text content or subsequent tool calls). The agent interpreted this as session completion and exited the loop.

## Solution

**File**: `packages/opencode/src/session/prompt.ts:368-376`

**Change**: Added content presence check for the last assistant message before exiting the loop.

```typescript
// BEFORE
if (
  lastAssistant?.finish &&
  !["tool-calls", "unknown"].includes(lastAssistant.finish) &&
  lastUser.id < lastAssistant.id
) {
  break
}

// AFTER
const lastAssistantMsg = msgs.find(m => m.info.id === lastAssistant?.id)
const hasContent = lastAssistantMsg && lastAssistantMsg.parts.some(p => p.type === "text" || p.type === "tool")
if (
  lastAssistant?.finish &&
  !["tool-calls", "unknown"].includes(lastAssistant.finish) &&
  lastUser.id < lastAssistant.id &&
  hasContent  // ← NEW CHECK
) {
  break
}
```

## Logic

The agent now exits the loop only if:

1. `finish` is not `"tool-calls"` or `"unknown"`
2. The last user message is older than the last assistant message
3. **NEW**: Assistant message contains content (text or tool)

If Qwen sends an empty message with `finish="stop"`, the agent does not exit the loop and waits for the next iteration.

